<paragraph blockId="5.[761,1354,1582,2010]" lastBlockId="5.[146,1356,2017,3470]" pageId="5" pageNumber="439">
Description of 
<taxonomicName box="[1002,1121,1740,1773]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Pleronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="439" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="macleayii">macleayii</taxonomicName>
was associated with three specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1154,1228,1780,1813]" name="Cuba" pageId="5" pageNumber="439">Cuba</collectingCountry>
presented by W. S. Macleay to J. E. Gray; original description was detailed and accurate and apparently based on only one male among these specimens. It is believed that such material, however, contained both species of Antillean mustached bats, 
<taxonomicName box="[783,942,2017,2050]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Pleronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="439" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="macleayii">P. macleayii</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gundlach" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1023,1207,2017,2050]" class="Mammalia" family="Mormoopidae" genus="Pteronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="439" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="quadridens">P. quadridens</taxonomicName>
, and that during World WarII, the incorrect specimen (an individual of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gundlach" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1044,1221,2056,2089]" class="Mammalia" family="Mormoopidae" genus="Pteronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="439" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="quadridens">P. quadridens</taxonomicName>
) was segregated as the holotype of 
<taxonomicName box="[535,689,2096,2129]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Pleronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="439" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="macleayii">P. macleayii</taxonomicName>
and subsequently labeled. J. D. Smith in 1972 designated another of these specimens as the holotype. Fossil records of P. macleayu: are reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[426,643,2174,2207]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="5" pageNumber="439">the Dominican</collectingCountry>
Republic and New Providence Island, 
<collectingCountry box="[1216,1346,2174,2207]" name="Bahamas" pageId="5" pageNumber="439">Bahamas</collectingCountry>
, suggesting a more extensive distribution in the late Quaternary than today. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
